1
00:00:18,350 --> 00:00:18,760
Xiaozhou.

2
00:00:18,760 --> 00:00:20,070
Just a moment, Uncle Shi.

3
00:00:20,070 --> 00:00:20,870
Have some water.

4
00:00:20,870 --> 00:00:21,530
Take a rest.

5
00:00:21,670 --> 00:00:22,510
I'm okay, Dad.

6
00:00:22,640 --> 00:00:23,830
Mom, take a break. Let me take over.

7
00:00:23,830 --> 00:00:24,960
I don't need to rest.

8
00:00:24,960 --> 00:00:25,760
I'm not tired.

9
00:00:26,190 --> 00:00:27,510
Uncle Shi, you want two, right?

10
00:00:27,510 --> 00:00:28,440
Yes, two.

11
00:00:28,510 --> 00:00:29,830
Come on, Xiaohai,

12
00:00:29,830 --> 00:00:30,760
have some water.

13
00:00:32,470 --> 00:00:33,430
I just went to your house

14
00:00:33,430 --> 00:00:34,390
and saw no one was home,

15
00:00:34,390 --> 00:00:35,030
so I brought it here.

16
00:00:35,030 --> 00:00:35,960
Here. Over here.

17
00:00:36,200 --> 00:00:38,150
It must be the college admission letter,
right?

18
00:00:38,150 --> 00:00:38,790
Thank you.

19
00:00:40,600 --> 00:00:41,600
She got admitted?

20
00:00:43,960 --> 00:00:44,920
Yes, she got admitted.

21
00:00:44,920 --> 00:00:46,790
-The admission letter.
-You got in.

22
00:00:46,790 --> 00:00:48,280
Xiaozhou, that's impressive!

23
00:00:48,280 --> 00:00:49,350
You're going places!

24
00:00:49,350 --> 00:00:50,000
Here you are.

25
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:52,530
Environmental and Scientific Engineering.

26
00:00:53,350 --> 00:00:54,410
Admission letter.

27
00:00:55,390 --> 00:00:57,250
Your sister's admission letter.

28
00:00:57,840 --> 00:00:59,640
Liu, take your money back.

29
00:01:00,100 --> 00:01:01,900
-It's on me today.
-Take it back.

30
00:01:02,110 --> 00:01:03,030
Alright, alright.

31
00:01:03,030 --> 00:01:04,040
-Thank you.
-You're welcome.

32
00:01:04,040 --> 00:01:04,560
Thanks.

33
00:01:04,590 --> 00:01:05,870
Wang, Ma!

34
00:01:06,070 --> 00:01:06,930
Come over here!

35
00:01:07,040 --> 00:01:08,430
Today, I'm treating everyone!

36
00:01:08,430 --> 00:01:09,560
Everything's on me!

37
00:01:09,560 --> 00:01:10,450
Come eat for free!

38
00:01:10,450 --> 00:01:10,970
Great!

39
00:01:11,310 --> 00:01:12,150
For free!

40
00:01:12,480 --> 00:01:14,070
Congratulations!

41
00:01:14,280 --> 00:01:16,070
Congratulations on getting admitted.

42
00:01:16,070 --> 00:01:17,039
Thank you.

43
00:01:18,480 --> 00:01:19,710
Look at my dad.

44
00:02:53,510 --> 00:02:59,070
[Beneath the Undertow]

45
00:03:00,190 --> 00:03:02,670
[Episode 7]

46
00:03:09,840 --> 00:03:10,870
Is your son okay?

47
00:03:13,960 --> 00:03:14,800
Pull over.

48
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:16,930
You head back to the station first.

49
00:03:17,190 --> 00:03:18,360
Let me give you a ride.

50
00:03:18,360 --> 00:03:20,120
I know where
the Garden Road Traffic Police Station is.

51
00:03:20,120 --> 00:03:22,360
No need. Pull over.

52
00:03:22,560 --> 00:03:24,000
If I head back to the station first

53
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:25,030
and we meet up later,

54
00:03:25,030 --> 00:03:26,960
it'll be 10 kilometers round trip.

55
00:03:27,630 --> 00:03:29,960
Let's save our brigade some gas,
alright?

56
00:03:52,079 --> 00:03:53,750
The situation has been clarified.

57
00:03:53,750 --> 00:03:55,310
He was the one driving the car.

58
00:03:55,310 --> 00:03:56,630
As for the other two kids,

59
00:03:56,630 --> 00:03:58,360
their parents have already
taken them home.

60
00:03:58,360 --> 00:03:59,690
As for the repair costs,

61
00:03:59,910 --> 00:04:02,120
see if the other party is willing
to go through insurance

62
00:04:02,120 --> 00:04:02,960
or handle it some other way.

63
00:04:02,960 --> 00:04:04,490
That's up to you to work out.

64
00:04:06,520 --> 00:04:07,120
Thank you.

65
00:04:08,520 --> 00:04:10,380
What about the car that cut us off?

66
00:04:11,150 --> 00:04:13,120
He said a car suddenly changed lanes

67
00:04:13,120 --> 00:04:14,240
and cut them off,

68
00:04:14,520 --> 00:04:16,510
causing them to crash into the roadside.

69
00:04:16,510 --> 00:04:17,240
Don't worry.

70
00:04:17,390 --> 00:04:19,000
Once we identify the license plate,

71
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:20,660
we'll hold them responsible.

72
00:04:21,560 --> 00:04:23,680
But you were driving
without a license after all.

73
00:04:23,680 --> 00:04:24,800
According to the regulations,

74
00:04:24,800 --> 00:04:26,950
those under 16 are exempt from detention,

75
00:04:26,950 --> 00:04:28,310
but there's a 200 yuan fine.

76
00:04:28,310 --> 00:04:29,800
Since we're both police officers,

77
00:04:29,800 --> 00:04:32,600
who do you prefer to handle
the disciplinary talk?

78
00:04:33,480 --> 00:04:35,360
You do it. Don't go easy on him.

79
00:04:35,870 --> 00:04:38,480
Children of police officers
should especially obey the law

80
00:04:38,480 --> 00:04:40,800
and set an example for other kids,

81
00:04:41,090 --> 00:04:41,680
right?

82
00:04:43,830 --> 00:04:45,190
Shu, say something.

83
00:04:54,510 --> 00:04:57,310
From today until school starts,

84
00:04:58,190 --> 00:05:00,070
Mom will take you
to and from the tutoring class,

85
00:05:00,070 --> 00:05:01,920
and you're not allowed to go out
at any other time.

86
00:05:01,920 --> 00:05:03,000
I want to go stay at Grandma's.

87
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:03,730
What's that?

88
00:05:04,270 --> 00:05:05,120
I want to go to Grandma's!

89
00:05:05,120 --> 00:05:05,920
Not possible!

90
00:05:06,720 --> 00:05:08,190
You're never home. Why do you care?

91
00:05:08,190 --> 00:05:09,490
Stop arguing, both of you.

92
00:05:09,490 --> 00:05:10,880
[Accident Unit, Pingning Brigade]

93
00:05:10,880 --> 00:05:11,880
Take him home first.

94
00:05:11,880 --> 00:05:13,010
We'll talk tonight.

95
00:05:14,560 --> 00:05:16,090
No arguing tonight either.

96
00:05:16,600 --> 00:05:19,330
Take him to the hospital
for a full-body checkup!

97
00:05:28,160 --> 00:05:28,950
Your son

98
00:05:30,390 --> 00:05:31,750
doesn't take after you much.

99
00:05:31,750 --> 00:05:33,610
He's got quite some personality.

100
00:05:34,430 --> 00:05:35,070
Drive.

101
00:05:37,070 --> 00:05:38,930
Did you lose your temper just now?

102
00:05:40,600 --> 00:05:42,060
First time I've seen that.

103
00:05:42,240 --> 00:05:43,570
You're too calm at work,

104
00:05:43,920 --> 00:05:44,950
always keeping your cool.

105
00:05:44,950 --> 00:05:46,800
But once you get home,
your temper flares up,

106
00:05:46,800 --> 00:05:47,870
and you take it all out on your family.

107
00:05:47,870 --> 00:05:48,830
That's not good.

108
00:05:49,950 --> 00:05:52,350
Have you always treated your son
like this?

109
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:55,120
By the way,

110
00:05:55,950 --> 00:05:58,750
your wife seems quite easygoing.

111
00:05:58,870 --> 00:06:00,670
She must be a really kind person.

112
00:06:00,830 --> 00:06:03,360
Fortunately, your son has
such a good mother.

113
00:06:04,040 --> 00:06:06,600
Your wife's temperament
is really different from yours.

114
00:06:06,600 --> 00:06:07,680
When did you two meet?

115
00:06:07,680 --> 00:06:08,680
Are you finished?

116
00:06:11,560 --> 00:06:13,290
I'm just making conversation.

117
00:06:15,510 --> 00:06:16,950
They've sent information

118
00:06:16,950 --> 00:06:19,030
on Zhang Haoyang's case's witnesses.

119
00:06:19,030 --> 00:06:21,960
Or do you want to deal with
your family matters first?

120
00:06:25,920 --> 00:06:26,510
Let's go.

121
00:06:30,560 --> 00:06:31,630
This Jia Beibei

122
00:06:31,830 --> 00:06:33,690
came to Lingchuan this February.

123
00:06:33,830 --> 00:06:35,600
She doesn't have any relatives
or friends here,

124
00:06:35,600 --> 00:06:37,040
and has been looking for a job.

125
00:06:37,040 --> 00:06:39,120
She used to work as a waitress
at a Japanese restaurant,

126
00:06:39,120 --> 00:06:40,270
but she wasn't committed to her work

127
00:06:40,270 --> 00:06:41,120
and couldn't learn anything,

128
00:06:41,120 --> 00:06:42,630
so she got fired not long after.

129
00:06:42,630 --> 00:06:43,120
Usually,

130
00:06:43,120 --> 00:06:45,240
she likes posting lifestyle videos online,

131
00:06:45,240 --> 00:06:46,040
ordering takeout,

132
00:06:46,040 --> 00:06:47,600
putting on makeup, buying little things,

133
00:06:47,600 --> 00:06:49,310
decorating her rental apartment,
and stuff like that.

134
00:06:49,310 --> 00:06:50,510
Ying, play the video.

135
00:06:51,070 --> 00:06:52,750
I've got new nails done.

136
00:06:52,770 --> 00:06:54,920
They look better than
the bright red color from last week,

137
00:06:54,920 --> 00:06:56,270
making my feet look whiter.

138
00:06:56,270 --> 00:06:58,470
I happen to be soaking my feet right now.

139
00:06:58,800 --> 00:07:00,930
Also, check out my new toenail polish.

140
00:07:01,160 --> 00:07:02,360
Looks good, right?

141
00:07:02,920 --> 00:07:05,190
I really love this color.

142
00:07:05,510 --> 00:07:07,560
Doesn't it make my feet look super white

143
00:07:07,560 --> 00:07:09,870
and my skin look really good?

144
00:07:11,270 --> 00:07:14,000
We're tracking the source of
the molding materials,

145
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:16,190
both online and offline retail channels,

146
00:07:16,190 --> 00:07:18,920
including manufacturers in Shandong,
Dongguan, and Shenzhen,

147
00:07:18,920 --> 00:07:20,560
but we haven't found anything yet.

148
00:07:20,560 --> 00:07:22,290
The murderer is quite skilled,

149
00:07:22,560 --> 00:07:24,870
with rather strong
counter-investigation awareness.

150
00:07:24,870 --> 00:07:26,270
A bit too strong, okay?

151
00:07:27,050 --> 00:07:29,040
With surveillance cameras
almost everywhere nowadays,

152
00:07:29,040 --> 00:07:29,950
we still haven't figured out

153
00:07:29,950 --> 00:07:31,160
where Jia Beibei

154
00:07:31,160 --> 00:07:32,310
last encountered the murderer.

155
00:07:32,310 --> 00:07:34,070
Based on her last known movements,

156
00:07:34,070 --> 00:07:37,159
she most likely went with the murderer
at the beach.

157
00:07:37,950 --> 00:07:41,430
The place where Wang Yishan

158
00:07:42,159 --> 00:07:44,420
was last seen is likely also at the beach.

159
00:07:48,159 --> 00:07:50,190
I didn't know we had such a nice place
around here.

160
00:07:50,190 --> 00:07:51,520
Is it open to the public?

161
00:07:52,560 --> 00:07:54,890
Yes, as long as you
pay the membership fee.

162
00:07:57,310 --> 00:07:59,510
Where were you on the night of June 19th?

163
00:07:59,920 --> 00:08:01,390
The night of the murder?

164
00:08:03,040 --> 00:08:03,640
Drinking.

165
00:08:06,270 --> 00:08:07,670
Was Zhang Haoyang there?

166
00:08:09,240 --> 00:08:09,950
Yes.

167
00:08:10,600 --> 00:08:12,400
We were drinking because of him.

168
00:08:12,680 --> 00:08:13,830
He got dumped.

169
00:08:14,240 --> 00:08:15,370
Where did you drink?

170
00:08:16,040 --> 00:08:17,270
At a buddy's place.

171
00:08:18,720 --> 00:08:19,720
Specific address?

172
00:08:19,720 --> 00:08:21,850
No idea. Who remembers house numbers?

173
00:08:22,170 --> 00:08:23,230
Whose place was it?

174
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:29,040
I forgot.
I was just there to join the fun.

175
00:08:29,040 --> 00:08:30,970
Why would I care whose place it was?

176
00:08:35,150 --> 00:08:36,210
Stop slacking off.

177
00:08:36,750 --> 00:08:37,870
We're talking to you.

178
00:08:37,870 --> 00:08:39,530
I'm a witness, not a criminal.

179
00:08:39,909 --> 00:08:41,710
I'm not obligated to answer you.

180
00:08:45,440 --> 00:08:47,480
Move aside, or I'll hit the ball.

181
00:08:47,750 --> 00:08:48,320
Go ahead.

182
00:08:52,960 --> 00:08:54,020
Don't be like that.

183
00:08:56,840 --> 00:08:57,860
You actually have a job?

184
00:08:57,860 --> 00:08:59,740
Yes, at an advertising company.

185
00:09:00,240 --> 00:09:01,550
Your father's company, right?

186
00:09:01,550 --> 00:09:02,080
No.

187
00:09:02,270 --> 00:09:04,080
I want to open
my own advertising company someday,

188
00:09:04,080 --> 00:09:06,210
so I'm getting some experience first.

189
00:09:06,980 --> 00:09:08,570
On the evening of June 19th,

190
00:09:08,600 --> 00:09:11,060
you guys were drinking at your place,
right?

191
00:09:11,080 --> 00:09:11,910
Yes, at my place.

192
00:09:11,910 --> 00:09:12,640
I live alone.

193
00:09:12,780 --> 00:09:14,440
Until what time did you drink?

194
00:09:14,750 --> 00:09:16,600
Until after 1 AM, I think.

195
00:09:17,090 --> 00:09:18,950
I could barely get up the next day.

196
00:09:19,970 --> 00:09:22,170
What happened to Zhang Haoyang's hand?

197
00:09:22,720 --> 00:09:23,790
His hand?

198
00:09:25,770 --> 00:09:26,440
He was drunk

199
00:09:26,470 --> 00:09:27,750
and cut his hand on a bottle.

200
00:09:27,750 --> 00:09:30,280
Otherwise, we wouldn't have ended
the party.

201
00:09:32,240 --> 00:09:35,630
You don't suspect Zhang Haoyang, do you?

202
00:09:35,870 --> 00:09:36,910
He wouldn't do something like that.

203
00:09:36,910 --> 00:09:38,840
He's a model citizen in our circle.

204
00:09:39,200 --> 00:09:40,000
Is that so?

205
00:09:40,730 --> 00:09:41,960
You probably don't know,

206
00:09:41,960 --> 00:09:43,270
but Zhang Haoyang's parents

207
00:09:43,270 --> 00:09:45,070
divorced when he was very young.

208
00:09:45,380 --> 00:09:46,870
He'd been living with his mother
ever since.

209
00:09:46,870 --> 00:09:48,670
Then, when he was in high school,

210
00:09:48,670 --> 00:09:49,840
his mother passed away.

211
00:09:49,840 --> 00:09:51,790
His father never had another son,

212
00:09:52,070 --> 00:09:53,240
so he took him back.

213
00:09:53,360 --> 00:09:54,910
Even though, like us,

214
00:09:54,910 --> 00:09:56,480
he doesn't have to worry about money,

215
00:09:56,480 --> 00:09:58,080
he's not flashy at all,

216
00:09:58,080 --> 00:09:59,000
very low-key.

217
00:09:59,000 --> 00:09:59,870
At first, when his father

218
00:09:59,870 --> 00:10:01,670
took him to various gatherings,

219
00:10:01,750 --> 00:10:03,030
he was really uncomfortable.

220
00:10:03,030 --> 00:10:04,750
Later, he got a bit better,

221
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:06,800
and started hanging out with us.

222
00:10:06,910 --> 00:10:07,840
We all know that

223
00:10:07,870 --> 00:10:09,840
he's been pursuing someone relentlessly,

224
00:10:09,840 --> 00:10:11,790
that college girl,

225
00:10:11,870 --> 00:10:13,330
but none of us have met her.

226
00:10:13,480 --> 00:10:14,870
With Zhang Haoyang's personality,

227
00:10:14,870 --> 00:10:16,800
he wouldn't even step on an insect,

228
00:10:16,870 --> 00:10:18,200
let alone kill someone.

229
00:10:18,320 --> 00:10:19,720
That's just impossible.

230
00:10:20,150 --> 00:10:22,280
If there's nothing else, I'll just...

231
00:10:22,870 --> 00:10:23,360
Okay.

232
00:10:27,910 --> 00:10:29,970
Do you think what he said is credible?

233
00:10:32,150 --> 00:10:34,150
We should remain skeptical for now.

234
00:10:34,790 --> 00:10:35,630
Who's next?

235
00:10:37,670 --> 00:10:38,910
Not a good guy.

236
00:10:40,030 --> 00:10:40,750
Here you go.

237
00:10:42,200 --> 00:10:42,840
And yours.

238
00:10:47,080 --> 00:10:48,270
Import and export?

239
00:10:49,320 --> 00:10:50,780
What do you actually sell?

240
00:10:50,910 --> 00:10:52,240
Whatever interests me.

241
00:10:53,120 --> 00:10:53,960
Like this,

242
00:10:54,360 --> 00:10:58,020
and the sofas and lamps over there.
They're all limited editions.

243
00:10:59,480 --> 00:11:01,030
I sell this as well.

244
00:11:02,600 --> 00:11:05,200
Basically, I sell anything
that interests me.

245
00:11:05,390 --> 00:11:07,240
I just want to make my life

246
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:09,330
a bit more comfortable.

247
00:11:09,440 --> 00:11:11,040
And the wine we drank that day

248
00:11:11,120 --> 00:11:12,380
was brought over by me.

249
00:11:14,630 --> 00:11:17,560
You're the leader of this little circle,
aren't you?

250
00:11:19,270 --> 00:11:20,080
Not really.

251
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:23,000
They just respect me.

252
00:11:25,200 --> 00:11:27,480
How's your relationship
with Zhang Haoyang?

253
00:11:27,480 --> 00:11:28,670
Do you know him well?

254
00:11:28,960 --> 00:11:31,200
Haoyang? He's my buddy.

255
00:11:32,200 --> 00:11:35,510
I shouldn't talk about
a friend behind his back,

256
00:11:36,840 --> 00:11:37,970
but since you asked,

257
00:11:38,390 --> 00:11:39,390
I have to tell you.

258
00:11:39,840 --> 00:11:42,480
Haoyang is a nice guy,

259
00:11:43,080 --> 00:11:44,000
but

260
00:11:45,240 --> 00:11:46,240
he's rather weak.

261
00:11:47,370 --> 00:11:49,310
After going back to live with his father,

262
00:11:49,310 --> 00:11:51,100
his living environment changed suddenly,

263
00:11:51,100 --> 00:11:52,430
and he felt pretty lost.

264
00:11:52,960 --> 00:11:54,670
His father wanted him
to take over the family business,

265
00:11:54,670 --> 00:11:58,440
but he wasn't interested in the whole
calligraphy, painting, and jade thing.

266
00:11:58,440 --> 00:11:59,570
He felt pretty lost,

267
00:12:00,150 --> 00:12:02,410
and that's when he met... Shen Xiaozhou.

268
00:12:03,400 --> 00:12:04,870
Did I say it right?
It's Shen Xiaozhou, right?

269
00:12:04,870 --> 00:12:06,670
Have you ever met Shen Xiaozhou?

270
00:12:06,870 --> 00:12:07,480
No.

271
00:12:07,960 --> 00:12:10,820
Haoyang wouldn't let us meet her.
He's possessive.

272
00:12:15,870 --> 00:12:17,840
But Haoyang told us

273
00:12:18,670 --> 00:12:19,840
that this girl

274
00:12:20,760 --> 00:12:22,120
has helped him a lot.

275
00:12:22,480 --> 00:12:24,790
Many times when he didn't know what to do,

276
00:12:25,200 --> 00:12:27,030
this girl gave him a lot of encouragement.

277
00:12:27,030 --> 00:12:28,200
In Haoyang's words,

278
00:12:28,550 --> 00:12:31,510
that girl's like a sunflower.

279
00:12:31,510 --> 00:12:33,310
